I am not sure I really understand  the incentives here:Melvin Capital Manag=
ement=E2=80=99s traders pocketed hefty performance fees over a half-decade =
while achieving roughly 30% in annualized gains. Now, after a streak of ste=
ep losses, they=E2=80=99re abruptly returning client cash and moving on.Som=
e of Melvin=E2=80=99s investors caught flat-footed this week by Gabe Plotki=
n=E2=80=99s decision to shut his hedge fund are grousing privately about fa=
ir-weather money management. They were hopeful his team could recoup at lea=
st some of the money it started losing in a short-squeeze more than a year =
ago and try to make them whole.Instead, Plotkin announced Wednesday he=E2=
=80=99s already winding down Melvin=E2=80=99s portfolio, effectively freein=
g some 40 employees at the firm from working below the so-called high-water=
 mark that they=E2=80=99d have to crest to resume performance fees.=E2=80=
=9COnly in hedge-fund-land does someone get paid hundreds and hundreds of m=
illions of dollars on Jan. 1, incinerate half of clients=E2=80=99 capital a=
 few weeks later, fail to recover over the next year or so, then suddenly s=
hut the doors,=E2=80=9D said Andrew Beer, managing member of New York-based=
 Dynamic Beta Investments, a firm that seeks to replicate hedge fund return=
s. He=E2=80=99s not an investor in Melvin, but echoed the sentiments of som=
e who were.=E2=80=9CThere are plenty of hedge fund managers,=E2=80=9D he sa=
id, =E2=80=9Cwho were paid a lot one year, went through difficult drawdowns=
 then worked for years to claw their way back. Melvin obviously isn=E2=80=
=99t one of them.=E2=80=9DLike one thing that Plotkin could do would be:=09=
Say =E2=80=9Cokay everyone, fine, I=E2=80=99ll keep managing your money, an=
d won=E2=80=99t charge you any performance fees until we get back to our  h=
igh-water mark, just like you asked.=E2=80=9D=09Keep their money and contin=
ue charging a management fee of 1% or 2% of assets, collecting millions of =
dollars in fees even without performance fees.=09Fire all the analysts and =
keep the fees for himself.=09Spend five minutes a day picking stocks and th=
e rest of his time on the beach.=09If the stocks go up, hey great super, ma=
ybe one day there are performance fees again, whatever.=09If the stocks go =
down, the investors call and complain and he says =E2=80=9CHMMM MAYBE YOU S=
HOULD FIRE ME I DUNNO.=E2=80=9DIf I somehow got put in charge of a hedge fu=
nd, I am not sure I would be good at either the investing job of picking st=
ocks that will go up or at the investor-relations job of convincing allocat=
ors to let me manage their money. Both of those jobs seem challenging and c=
ompetitive. But if you put me in charge of a hedge fund where my mandate wa=
s to=C2=A0convince clients to withdraw their money, I bet I could manage it=
. That job seems easy!At some level I do understand the allocators who are =
like =E2=80=9Cyou lost all this money for me, now you have to keep managing=
 my money forever.=E2=80=9D[1]=C2=A0I am just saying that there are some pr=
oblems with that approach.Meanwhile you know who is happy about Melvin clos=
ing? Reddit:Plotkin=E2=80=99s decision to shut down his $7.8 billion fund w=
as met with celebration on the forums that fueled the initial revolt agains=
t his short positions in GameStop Corp. and other troubled companies that b=
ecame the favorite meme stocks of 2021. At the time, an army of traders on =
Reddit=E2=80=99s WallStreetBets targeted Melvin and other hedge funds, whic=
h they argued were a manifestation of Wall Street=E2=80=99s greed. =C2=A0=
=E2=80=9CThis is a victory parade day for everyone part of that movement,=
=E2=80=9D said Steve Khoe, who works in sales in Detroit and is part of Wal=
lStreetBets. =E2=80=9CIt's just joy and satisfaction, especially in the fac=
e of some of the negative market indicators these days.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6W=
allStreetBets moderator Jordan Zazzara said the outcome proves the power of=
 retail traders, and =E2=80=9Chas to hurt.=E2=80=9D=E2=80=9CMaybe it's not =
the best idea to pick a fight with and condescend to millions of people,=E2=
=80=9D he said.Yeah I dunno did you read the part about him getting paid hu=
ndreds of millions of dollars in fees? He gets to keep those.=C2=A0
