be to Money Stuff and other great Bloomberg newsletters here. Thanks![1] I =
do! We=E2=80=99ve  talked about this before. You could have a basic model l=
ike this (numbers made up for convenience): Plotkin is a skilled investor w=
ho on average compounds at 20% per year. The way that worked over the past =
few years is that he returned 49% per year for four years and then lost hal=
f the money in the fifth year. That works out to about a 20% compound annua=
