 over the first four years, and then didn=E2=80=99t give any of the money b=
ack when he lost money in the fifth year. So he was overpaid relative to hi=
s true performance. And the only way for his pay to be fair is for him to k=
eep managing money (and compounding at 20% on average) until he has earned =
back those performance fees =E2=80=94=C2=A0which he should be able to do be=
cause his =E2=80=9Ctrue=E2=80=9D performance is a 20% annual return. (Again=
 I should emphasize that I made up these numbers.)[2] He actually wrote =E2=
=80=9Chit price,=E2=80=9D not =E2=80=9Chit piece,=E2=80=9D which I assume i=
s a typo, though perhaps a Freudian one: He really would like to pay a lowe=
r price for Twitter.
